Students who are unable to fund their 2018 tertiary education are encouraged to apply for bursaries which are available from eThekwini Municipality. The closing date for all bursary applications is Thursday, 17 November. The bursaries will be awarded to students who are pursuing studies in the fields of Engineering, Architecture, Quantity Surveying, Science and Chemistry. A student relief fund is also available for undergraduates who are full time students at Public Higher Education Institutions. Applicants must be a South African citizen and intend on studying in one of the aforementioned fields of study. Interested individuals can obtain further information or the relevant application form at 11th Floor, Shell House, 221 Anton Lembede Street, Durban or contact the offices on 031 311 3192. 